 * What is not changing for our carriers?

       * How carriers invoice CCNA will NOT change. This will remain the same - via EDI, OTM and Manual (in some cases).

Helpful Tips 
- Please use the Palermo’s Sales Order number when scheduling pickup at CSW or PVI. Blujay 
identifies the Palermo’s Sales Order number as the Shipment Reference Number. 
Ex: Shipment Ref #(s) SO375200 
- Please use the customer order number when scheduling delivery. Blujay identifies the customer 
number as the Related Order Identifier. 
Ex: Related Order Identifier: 002801228086 
- Customer scheduling information is in the load report in Blujay. 
- When sending an email to Trans@palermospizza.com, please include “the Blujay number / SO 
Number / Customer or Destination” in the subject line 
Ex: 123456789 / SO654321 / Walmart Clarksville 
- Please send OSD issues directly to OSD@palermospizza.com and include 
Trans@palermospizza.com for increased visibility. Please include as much information about the 
incident as possible. The OSD team requests the following information to be included in the 
email: Palermo’s Order Number / Item Number / Quantity / Type of Issue. Please attach a copy 
of the customer signed POD and Pictures of the product, if applicable. 
- Please upload documentation when requesting accessorial rate changes 
- When closing a load in Blujay, please upload the POD and select the matching destination. 
Arrival and departure times are required for all stops. Please provide the most accurate time 
available.
For issues that require immediate assistance contact transportation@ruizfoods.com or Renee Robinson
